People who make things for gifts; please for the love of god make sure you think it through.
My father in law gives me exclusively anti gifts
Anti gifts are gifts where you’d have been better off getting nothing. The act of getting an anti gift makes you worse off
It’s something crafters tend to do
What did you get?
He made me an old timer tool box with my name on it, one of those wood ones with the dowel handle
Oh my
I have a nice tool box. There is no world where I junk that for this one
But he made it so I cannot junk it either
So I have to store it
Effectively he gave me the gift of less space in my garage
It was a double dip yesterday where I got that for my birthday and we got our Christmas gift of mini golf and lunch in Minneapolis.
In its own way driving 90 min each way to eat a burger and play mini golf is also an anti gift
Those were two “gifts” that were really gifts to himself. He wanted to make a thing and so he did, and he wanted to spend time with us so he did, but both were presented as things done for us.

Last year he got me a set of horseshoes and stakes. He likes horseshoes. I don’t care. So it’s a gift of best case more storage and worse case me losing a weekend building a horseshoe pit I’ll use twice a summer when he visits

As I typed this I was venting to my wife and she reminded me of the framed picture of them we got last year as a “gift”. We have no photographs in our house, and we’ve commented before we just don’t like family photos as art, so of course they gave us one of them.
#whitepeopleproblems
